Sentencas: In the present work, one dimensional La0.8Sr0.2Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) nanofibers with the mean diameter of about 100 nm prepared by electrospinning were deposited on Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (GDC) electrolyte followed by sintering to form one dimensional LSCF nanofiber cathode.
Titulo: Effect of La0.8Sr0.2Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ morphology on the performance of composite cathodes

Sentencas: And LSCF/GDC composite cathodes were formed by introducing GDC phases into LSCF nanofiber scaffold using infiltration method.
Titulo: Effect of La0.8Sr0.2Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ morphology on the performance of composite cathodes

Sentencas: The polarization resistances for the composite cathode with an optimal LSCF/GDC mass ratio of 1/0.56 are 0.27, 0.14 and 0.07 Omega cm(2) at 650, 700 and 750 degrees C, respectively, which are obviously smaller than 2.26, 0.78 and 0.29 Omega cm(2) of pure LSCF nanofiber cathode.
Titulo: Effect of La0.8Sr0.2Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ morphology on the performance of composite cathodes

Sentencas: And the activation energy is 1.194 eV, which is much lower than that of pure LSCF nanofiber cathode (1.684 eV).
Titulo: Effect of La0.8Sr0.2Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ morphology on the performance of composite cathodes

Sentencas: These results demonstrate that the infiltration of GDC into LSCF nanofiber scaffold is an effective approach to achieve high performance cathode for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Effect of La0.8Sr0.2Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ morphology on the performance of composite cathodes

Sentencas: In addition, the performance of composite cathode in this work was also compared with that of our previous nanorod structured LSCF/GDC composite cathode.
Titulo: Effect of La0.8Sr0.2Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ morphology on the performance of composite cathodes
